        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 2:54AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 253 AM CDT, the public reported strong thunderstorms along a line
extending from near Port Lavaca to near Bayside. Movement was
southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Observed at various ASOS.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Port Lavaca, Rockport, Refugio, Woodsboro, Seadrift, Port Oconnor,
Lamar, Point Comfort, Bayside, Quintana, Palm Harbor, Long Mott,
Green Lake, Bonnie View, Holiday Beach, Tivoli, Matagorda Island
State Park, Alamo Beach, Indianola, and Key Allegro.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 183 near mile marker 668.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 606 and 634.
US Highway 87 between mile markers 828 and 840.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
south central and south Texas.</instruction>
